Class Example

java.lang.Object
  br.usp.poli.takiyama.utils.Example

public class Example

Stores parfactors, logical variables, parameterized random variables (PRV) and other data structures used in AC-FOVE tests.

existsNetworkWithBX

public static Example existsNetworkWithBX(int domainSize)
Returns data structures corresponding to CRALC expression ∃r.b(X). It uses b(X) instead of b(Y) to test if context variables can be parameterized by the extra logical variable.

Parameters:
domainSize - The number of individuals of X.
Returns:
data structures corresponding to CRALC expression ∃r.b(X).

waterSprinklerNetWork

public static Example waterSprinklerNetWork(int domainSize)
Water sprinkler network proposed by Kevin Murphy. The network was adapted to a lifted version: sprinkler and wet_grass are random variables parameterized on a logical variable Lot. The original network is shown here: http://www.cs.ubc.ca/~murphyk/Bayes/bnintro.html The number of nodes in this network is 2 * (domainSize + 1)

Parameters:
domainSize -
Returns:

sickDeathNetwork

public static Example sickDeathNetwork(int domainSize)
The Sick and Death network used as example by Rodrigo de Salvo Braz in his IJCAI-05 paper. The network has been adapted to use aggregation parfactors by adding a 'someDeath' node. It also uses a directed graph to represent cause/consequence relations (the original is a Markov network).

The number of nodes in this network is 2 * (domainSize + 1)

Parameters:
domainSize -
Returns:

propositionalizeAll

public Marginal propositionalizeAll(Marginal marginal)
Returns the specified network completely propositionalized. The resulting network can be used with VE algorithms.

The resulting network will not have logical variables and factors (space constraint).

Parameters:
network - The network to propositionalize.
Returns:
the specified network completely propositionalized.

removeAggregation

public Marginal removeAggregation(Marginal marginal)
Returns the specified network with aggregation parfactors converted to standard parfactors. The resulting network can be used with the C-FOVE algorithm.

Parameters:
network - The network where aggregation parfactors will be converted
Returns:
The specified network with aggregation parfactors converted to standard parfactors.
